Reasoning: The paper deals with a graph parameter that has its origin in algebraic geometry, but the focus is on the computational complexity of determining this parameter. The use of an Integer Linear Programming instance suggests a connection to discrete mathematics (cs.DM), while the use of chip firing games and subdivisions of edges suggests a connection to computational geometry (cs.CG) and graph theory (cs.GT). The fact that the parameter is NP-complete suggests a connection to computational complexity (cs.CC) and the use of certificates suggests a connection to algorithms and data structures (cs.DS).
